Sadly enough, and as much as it pains me to agree, it is a poorly produced show, and the acting is even worse. Its not going to last, and usually if a show has good ratings past 13 episodes, thats when they start talking money, and renewing the show and so on. I highly doubt this will make it past the 13 shows, on TNT anyways. I know they already shot the 13, because you can read about it in different blogs, and they've showed some critics all 13 already, which they shouldnt have, because the critics shit all over it. I think it iwll make it to around 10 episodes, have very poor ratings, even for cable tv, and get sold off to a lesser network, MAYBE Sci-fi, where it will play out its 13 episodes, over and over and over. Sci-fi is way too cheap to pay noah willey and the rest of the cast to make new fresh episodes, and by no means could they ever afford Spileburg and Dreamworks. I know Spielburg is only exectutive producer on this, but come on, he needs to do better if his stamp is going to be on this pile of warm dog poo. Go watch the episode of The Totally Rad Show where they reviewed this show, they hit it spot on, the actors arent engaging enough, not enough of them anyways. The special effects are weak, and the plot line is weaker and predictable. The guy above said it BEST, its a Soap Opera with guns, lol.
